The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Plan for wetlands
                                                                                                               Plan for wetlands
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A comprehensive management plan for the East Calcutta Wetlands was unveiled at a meeting of the East Calcutta Wetlands Authority at Writers Buildings on Friday.        
	Chief secretary Asok Mohan Chakrabarti, who attended the meeting, directed the environment department to work out detailed sectoral plans and budgetary requirements, said M.L. Meena, the environment secretary and the member secretary of the authority.        
	The plan was prepared by Wetland Internationals. We will make a presentation after the elections, added Meena. The chief secretary also asked the authorities to stop encroachment of the wetlands.        
	The secretary of NGO Jalabhumi Banchao Committee, Tushar Ghosh, who attended the meeting, said a map of the wetlands had been prepared identifying water bodies, agricultural land and settlement areas.                                                                                                                                                                            
